The 7× table is the one everyone stumbles on. Let's print it and see the pattern.

<!-- BUILD: Prints the 7× table from 7 × 1 to 7 × 10. -->

```scheme
(define (times-table n limit)
  (map (lambda (k)
         (let ((product (* n k)))
           (display (string-append 
                      (number->string n) \" × \" 
                      (number->string k) \" = \" 
                      (number->string product)))
           (newline)
           product))
       (range 1 (+ limit 1))))

(times-table 7 10)
```

[VISUAL: A printed table:
