7 × 1 = 7
7 × 2 = 14
7 × 3 = 21
7 × 4 = 28
7 × 5 = 35
7 × 6 = 42
7 × 7 = 49
7 × 8 = 56
7 × 9 = 63
7 × 10 = 70
```
]

7, 14, 21, 28, 35, 42, 49, 56, 63, 70. No obvious shortcut, but the numbers are spaced evenly, seven apart. That *is* the pattern: each step adds 7.

