### Example 3.12: Doubling (Multiply by 2)

Doubling a number is multiplying it by 2. Let's write a function that doubles.

<!-- BUILD: Defines a (double n) function, prints double of 1 through 10. -->

```scheme
(define (double n)
  (* 2 n))

(map (lambda (k)
       (let ((result (double k)))
         (display (string-append 
                    \"double(\" (number->string k) \") = \" 
                    (number->string result)))
         (newline)
         result))
     (range 1 11))
```

