### Example 3.21: Dividing by 1 (No Change)

What happens when you divide by 1?

<!-- BUILD: Prints n ÷ 1 for n from 1 to 10. -->

```scheme
(define (division-table divisor limit)
  (map (lambda (k)
         (let ((n k))
           (display (string-append 
                      (number->string n) \" ÷ \" 
                      (number->string divisor) \" = \" 
                      (number->string (quotient n divisor))))
           (newline)
           (quotient n divisor)))
       (range 1 (+ limit 1))))

(division-table 1 10)
```

[VISUAL: A printed table:
```
1 ÷ 1 = 1
2 ÷ 1 = 2
3 ÷ 1 = 3
4 ÷ 1 = 4
5 ÷ 1 = 5
6 ÷ 1 = 6
7 ÷ 1 = 7
8 ÷ 1 = 8
9 ÷ 1 = 9
10 ÷ 1 = 10
```
]

Dividing by 1 leaves the number unchanged. **n ÷ 1 = n**.

